  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use: pre-market submission support for Class II CPB device, flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–4000 RPM, adult patient population. Structured hasContextOfUse is intentionally absent per ProfileMinimal declaration.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cpb-mrl2-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
