      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalized Index of Hemolysis comparison — CFD vs. in vitro at 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against FDA benchmark experimental data at 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min; maximum relative error 8.3%, within the 10% acceptance criterion for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/pressure-rise-comparison-2024",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-rise validation against experimental performance curve",
      "description": "Simulated pressure rise at each operating point agrees with measured values to within 5% across the full CPB flow-rate envelope, confirming hydraulic fidelity of the CFD model."
    }
  ],
